text: Texel is a municipality of the province of North Holland, the Netherlands. In 2016 the municipality had about 13,600 people. The municipality covers an area of 463 km², the island an area of 161 km². Texel makes part of the West Frisian Islands (Dutch: Waddeneilanden). It lies southwest of the island of Vlieland and northeast of the small island of Noorderhaaks (part of the municipality of Texel). Main town is Den Burg. == Other websites == * Category:West Frisian Islands
